Eskom spokesperson Khulu Phasiwe confirmed that Molefe had quit in a series of tweets posted on Friday afternoon. Eskom CEO Brian Molefe today announced that he'll voluntarily step down from Eskom with effect from 1 January 2017, said Phasiwe. Mr Molefe says he'll take take time off to reflect before deciding on his next career move, Phasiwe said that Molefe s stepping down was not an act of admission of wrongdoing on his part . Molefe has come under the spotlight in the last week for appearing in Public Protector s State of Capture report. The report paints his close relationship with the controversial Gupta family and also questions the sale of Glencore s Optimum mine to Tegeta.